cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the analysis and design of convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also discusses the expressive power of convolutional networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these fields are closely related to deep learning. Finally, the paper also involves mathematical analysis and tensor decompositions, which could fall under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
